title <size:18>Online Auction System with Mediator Pattern (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Seller lists a vintage watch. 3 bidders place bids. Auction mediator coordinates: validates, broadcasts, tracks highest bid, ends auction, notifies winner."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: AUCTION MEDIATOR — The Core Pattern (KEY)
' ====================================================================
interface AuctionMediator <<Mediator>> {
    + registerParticipant(participant) : void
    + placeBid(bidder, auctionId, amount) : BidResult
    + createAuction(seller, item, startPrice, endTime) : Auction
    + endAuction(auctionId) : AuctionResult
    + getAuctionStatus(auctionId) : AuctionStatus
    + notifyParticipants(auctionId, event) : void
}

class AuctionHouse <<ConcreteMediator>> {
    - auctions : Map<String, Auction>
    - participants : Map<String, AuctionParticipant>
    - bidValidator : BidValidator
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - paymentService : PaymentService
    --
    + registerParticipant(participant) : void
    + placeBid(bidder, auctionId, amount) : BidResult
    + createAuction(seller, item, startPrice, endTime) : Auction
    + endAuction(auctionId) : AuctionResult
    + getAuctionStatus(auctionId) : AuctionStatus
    + notifyParticipants(auctionId, event) : void
    + getActiveAuctions() : List<Auction>
    + getAuctionsForSeller(sellerId) : List<Auction>
}

note top of AuctionMediator #FFCDD2
    **STEP 1 - The Mediator. (THE KEY PATTERN)**
    "**Why Mediator here?** In an auction, sellers,
    bidders, and the auction itself all need to
    communicate. Without Mediator:"

    "Bidder1 -> Auction -> Bidder2 (notify outbid)
    Bidder1 -> Seller (notify new bid)
    Auction -> Bidder3 (notify outbid)
    ... N*N direct connections = chaos."

    "**With Mediator (AuctionHouse):**
    ALL communication goes through one hub.
    Bidder1 -> AuctionHouse -> routes to everyone.
    Participants never talk to each other directly.
    Bidder doesn't know about other bidders.
    Seller doesn't know who's bidding."

    "placeBid(): mediator validates, updates auction,
    notifies outbid bidder, notifies seller, broadcasts
    new highest bid. ONE method, all coordination."
    **Pattern: Mediator | SRP, Low Coupling**
end note

AuctionMediator <|.. AuctionHouse


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: PARTICIPANTS — Colleagues (don't know each other)
' ====================================================================
abstract class AuctionParticipant <<Colleague>> {
    - participantId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - mediator : AuctionMediator
    --
    + AuctionParticipant(id, name, email, mediator)
    + getId() : String
    + getName() : String
    + getEmail() : String
    + {abstract} receiveNotification(event) : void
}

class Seller {
    - listings : List<Auction>
    --
    + listItem(item, startPrice, endTime) : Auction
    + cancelAuction(auctionId) : void
    + receiveNotification(event) : void
}

class Bidder {
    - activeBids : Map<String, Bid>
    - wonAuctions : List<Auction>
    - maxAutoBid : Map<String, Double>
    --
    + placeBid(auctionId, amount) : BidResult
    + setAutoBid(auctionId, maxAmount) : void
    + receiveNotification(event) : void
}

note top of AuctionParticipant #FFE0B2
    **STEP 2 - Participants are "Colleagues".**
    "In Mediator pattern, participants are called
    **Colleagues**. They hold a reference to the
    Mediator but NEVER to each other."

    "**Seller** lists items via mediator:
    listItem() -> mediator.createAuction()."

    "**Bidder** places bids via mediator:
    placeBid() -> mediator.placeBid()."

    "**Neither knows about the other.**
    Seller doesn't know who's bidding.
    Bidder doesn't know who the seller is.
    All communication goes through AuctionHouse."

    "**receiveNotification()**: the mediator
    calls this to push events to participants."
    **Pattern: Mediator (Colleague) | Low Coupling**
end note

AuctionParticipant <|-- Seller
AuctionParticipant <|-- Bidder
AuctionParticipant --> AuctionMediator : communicates via >
AuctionHouse o--> AuctionParticipant : coordinates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: AUCTION + ITEM MODELS
' ====================================================================
class Auction {
    - auctionId : String
    - item : AuctionItem
    - seller : Seller
    - startPrice : double
    - currentHighestBid : Bid
    - bids : List<Bid>
    - bidders : Set<Bidder>
    - startTime : LocalDateTime
    - endTime : LocalDateTime
    - currentState : AuctionState
    - status : AuctionStatus
    - reservePrice : double
    --
    + placeBid(bid) : void
    + getHighestBid() : Bid
    + isActive() : bool
    + hasReserveMet() : bool
    + getBidCount() : int
    + getTimeRemaining() : long
    + getRegisteredBidders() : Set<Bidder>
}

class AuctionItem {
    - itemId : String
    - title : String
    - description : String
    - category : ItemCategory
    - images : List<String>
    - condition : ItemCondition
    --
    + getTitle() : String
    + getCategory() : ItemCategory
}

class Bid {
    - bidId : String
    - bidder : Bidder
    - auctionId : String
    - amount : double
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - isAutoBid : bool
    --
    + getAmount() : double
    + getBidder() : Bidder
    + getTimestamp() : LocalDateTime
}

enum AuctionStatus {
    DRAFT
    ACTIVE
    ENDED
    SOLD
    UNSOLD
    CANCELLED
}

enum ItemCategory {
    ELECTRONICS
    COLLECTIBLES
    ART
    JEWELRY
    VEHICLES
    ANTIQUES
}

enum ItemCondition {
    NEW
    LIKE_NEW
    USED_GOOD
    USED_FAIR
}

class AuctionResult {
    - auction : Auction
    - winner : Bidder
    - winningBid : Bid
    - finalPrice : double
    - sold : bool
    - reason : String
}

note top of Auction #C8E6C9
    **STEP 3 - Auction and bids.**
    "**Auction** is the central object: item, seller,
    bids list, current highest bid, start/end time,
    reserve price (minimum to sell), and state."

    "**Bid** records: who bid, how much, when,
    and whether it was an auto-bid."

    "**AuctionItem**: what's being sold — title,
    category, condition, images."

    "**AuctionResult**: outcome when auction ends.
    sold=true if highest bid >= reservePrice."
end note

Auction --> AuctionItem : for item >
Auction --> Seller : listed by >
Auction *-- Bid : has bids >
Auction --> AuctionStatus
Bid --> Bidder : by >
AuctionItem --> ItemCategory
AuctionItem --> ItemCondition
AuctionHouse o--> Auction : manages >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: AUCTION STATE — State Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface AuctionState <<State>> {
    + placeBid(auction, bid) : void
    + endAuction(auction) : AuctionResult
    + cancelAuction(auction) : void
    + startAuction(auction) : void
}

class DraftState {
    + startAuction(auction) : void
    + cancelAuction(auction) : void
}

class ActiveState {
    + placeBid(auction, bid) : void
    + endAuction(auction) : AuctionResult
    + cancelAuction(auction) : void
}

class EndedState {
    ' terminal — auction closed
}

class CancelledState {
    ' terminal — seller cancelled
}

note bottom of AuctionState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Auction lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — each state enforces rules."

    "**DraftState**: seller setting up. Can start
    or cancel. Cannot accept bids.
    **ActiveState**: live. Can accept bids, can
    end (time expires), can cancel.
    ActiveState.placeBid() validates bid > current
    highest, updates auction.
    **EndedState**: time up. If highestBid >= reserve
    -> SOLD. Else -> UNSOLD.
    **CancelledState**: terminal."

    "ActiveState.placeBid() is where the Mediator
    triggers: validate -> update -> notify outbid
    bidder -> notify seller -> broadcast."
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

AuctionState <|.. DraftState
AuctionState <|.. ActiveState
AuctionState <|.. EndedState
AuctionState <|.. CancelledState
Auction --> AuctionState : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: BID VALIDATION — Chain of Responsibility
' ====================================================================
abstract class BidValidator <<Handler>> {
    # next : BidValidator
    --
    + setNext(validator) : BidValidator
    + {abstract} validate(bid, auction) : ValidationResult
}

class MinIncrementValidator {
    - minIncrementPercent : double
    --
    + validate(bid, auction) : ValidationResult
}

class AuctionActiveValidator {
    + validate(bid, auction) : ValidationResult
}

class BidderEligibilityValidator {
    + validate(bid, auction) : ValidationResult
}

class SelfBidValidator {
    + validate(bid, auction) : ValidationResult
}

class BidResult {
    - success : bool
    - message : String
    - bid : Bid
    - newHighest : bool
}

note bottom of BidValidator #FFE0B2
    **STEP 5 - Validate the bid.**
    "**Chain of Responsibility:**
    1. **AuctionActiveValidator**: is auction live?
    2. **SelfBidValidator**: seller can't bid on
       own item!
    3. **BidderEligibilityValidator**: bidder not
       banned/suspended?
    4. **MinIncrementValidator**: bid must be at
       least 5% higher than current highest."

    "Mediator runs this chain before accepting
    any bid. Add ReservePriceValidator?
    Insert in chain."
    **Pattern: Chain of Responsibility | OCP, SRP**
end note

BidValidator <|-- MinIncrementValidator
BidValidator <|-- AuctionActiveValidator
BidValidator <|-- BidderEligibilityValidator
BidValidator <|-- SelfBidValidator
BidValidator o--> BidValidator : next >
AuctionHouse --> BidValidator : validates with >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: AUTO-BID — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface BiddingStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculateBid(auction, bidder, maxAmount) : double
}

class MinIncrementBiddingStrategy {
    - incrementPercent : double
    --
    + calculateBid(auction, bidder, maxAmount) : double
}

class AggressiveBiddingStrategy {
    --
    + calculateBid(auction, bidder, maxAmount) : double
}

class SniperBiddingStrategy {
    - snipeWindowSeconds : int
    --
    + calculateBid(auction, bidder, maxAmount) : double
}

note bottom of BiddingStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Auto-bidding.**
    "Bidder sets maxAutoBid = Rs 5000. When outbid,
    system auto-bids on their behalf."

    "**Strategy Pattern** — bidding algorithm:
    **MinIncrement**: bid current + 5% (conservative).
    **Aggressive**: bid 50% of remaining budget.
    **Sniper**: only bid in last 30 seconds."

    "When someone outbids, Mediator checks if
    outbid bidder has auto-bid enabled.
    If yes: strategy.calculateBid() -> auto place."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

BiddingStrategy <|.. MinIncrementBiddingStrategy
BiddingStrategy <|.. AggressiveBiddingStrategy
BiddingStrategy <|.. SniperBiddingStrategy
Bidder --> BiddingStrategy : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: MEDIATOR FLOW — The Core Interaction
' ====================================================================
note as MEDIATOR_FLOW #FFCDD2
    **STEP 7 - Mediator placeBid() flow. (KEY)**
    "Bidder1 calls bidder1.placeBid('A001', 5000)
    which calls mediator.placeBid(bidder1, 'A001', 5000):"

    "1. Look up Auction 'A001'
    2. Run BidValidator chain:
       Active? Yes. Self-bid? No. Eligible? Yes.
       MinIncrement? 5000 > 4500*1.05=4725? Yes.
    3. Create Bid object
    4. Auction.placeBid(bid) updates state
    5. **MEDIATOR COORDINATES all notifications:**
       a. Notify previous highest bidder (Bidder2):
          'You've been outbid on Vintage Watch!'
       b. Notify seller: 'New bid Rs 5000!'
       c. Broadcast to all watchers: 'New high bid!'
       d. Check Bidder2's auto-bid:
          If maxAutoBid=6000 -> auto-place 5250
          -> Repeat from step 2!"

    "**Without Mediator**: Bidder1 would need to know
    about Bidder2, Seller, watchers... tight coupling.
    **With Mediator**: Bidder1 only knows AuctionHouse."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: NOTIFICATION — Observer via Mediator
' ====================================================================
class AuctionEvent {
    - eventType : AuctionEventType
    - auction : Auction
    - bid : Bid
    - message : String
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
}

enum AuctionEventType {
    NEW_BID
    OUTBID
    AUCTION_STARTING
    AUCTION_ENDING_SOON
    AUCTION_ENDED
    AUCTION_WON
    AUCTION_CANCELLED
    RESERVE_MET
}

class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(participant, event) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class EmailNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class PushNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

note bottom of AuctionEvent #B2EBF2
    **STEP 8 - Notifications via Mediator.**
    "The Mediator replaces traditional Observer here.
    Instead of auction.notifyObservers(), the
    **Mediator decides** who gets notified:"

    "NEW_BID: notify seller + all watchers.
    OUTBID: notify the outbid bidder specifically.
    AUCTION_ENDING_SOON: notify all bidders.
    AUCTION_WON: notify winner + seller.
    AUCTION_CANCELLED: notify all bidders."

    "Notification channel via **Strategy**:
    Email, Push, SMS."
    **Mediator replaces Observer for coordination**
end note

AuctionEvent --> AuctionEventType
NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
AuctionHouse --> NotificationService : notifies via >
AuctionHouse --> AuctionEvent : creates >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 9: PAYMENT
' ====================================================================
class PaymentService {
    --
    + processPayment(winner, amount) : PaymentResult
    + processRefund(bidder, amount) : PaymentResult
}

class PaymentResult {
    - success : bool
    - transactionId : String
}

AuctionHouse --> PaymentService : on auction end >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Seller lists vintage watch via Mediator. 3 bidders
    place bids — all through AuctionHouse (Mediator). Bidder1 bids 5000.
    Mediator validates (**Chain**), updates auction (**State**: Active),
    notifies outbid Bidder2 ('You've been outbid!'), notifies Seller
    ('New bid Rs 5000!'), checks Bidder2's auto-bid (**Strategy**).
    Auction timer expires -> Mediator ends auction, announces winner,
    triggers payment."

    "**Why Mediator?** Without it, N bidders + seller + watchers =
    N*(N+1) direct connections. With Mediator: everyone talks to
    ONE hub. Add a new participant type (Auctioneer)? Register with
    Mediator. No existing participant changes."

    "6 patterns: **Mediator** (AuctionHouse — the star), **State**
    (auction lifecycle), **Chain of Responsibility** (bid validation),
    **Strategy** (x2: auto-bidding + notification), **Composition**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= Key Point |
    | 1 | AuctionHouse coordinates ALL communication between participants | Mediator | Participants never talk directly |
    | 2 | Seller lists item, Bidder places bid — both via Mediator only | Mediator (Colleague) | Low coupling between participants |
    | 3 | Auction: item, bids, highest bid, reserve, start/end time | Entity | Central domain object |
    | 4 | Draft -> Active -> Ended (Sold/Unsold) / Cancelled | State | Auction lifecycle with rules |
    | 5 | Active? Not self-bid? Eligible? Min increment met? | Chain of Responsibility | Sequential bid validation |
    | 6 | Auto-bid: MinIncrement / Aggressive / Sniper strategy | Strategy (bidding) | Automatic bidding on outbid |
    | 7 | Mediator.placeBid(): validate -> update -> notify ALL parties | Mediator Flow | ONE method, all coordination |
    | 8 | NEW_BID / OUTBID / WON / CANCELLED events via Email/Push/SMS | Strategy (notification) | Mediator decides who gets what |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Core**: Mediator = hub. Bidders/Sellers = spokes. No spoke-to-spoke communication. |  |  |
endlegend

@enduml
